@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

participant "Client" as Client
participant "<&clock> Timer" as Timer
participant "Coordinator" as Coord

' [step1 {"name":"Run 1: Start Write"}]
== Run 1 ==
Client -> Coord : start write
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"Run 1: Clock Advances"}]
Timer -> Timer : local time advances slowly
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"Run 1: Ack Still In Window"}]
Coord -> Coord : quorum ack still within timeout window
' [/step3]

' [step4 {"name":"Run 1: Success"}]
Coord -[#green]> Client : success
' [/step4]

' [step5 {"name":"Run 2: Start Write", "newPage":"true"}]
== Run 2 ==
Client -> Coord : start write
' [/step5]

' [step6 {"name":"Run 2: Clock Advances Faster"}]
Timer -> Timer : local time advances faster
' [/step6]

' [step7 {"name":"Run 2: Timeout Fires"}]
Timer -> Coord : timeout fires
' [/step7]

' [step8 {"name":"Run 2: Timeout Failure"}]
Coord -[#red]x Client : timeout failure
' [/step8]

note over Client, Coord
The same operation can cross a timeout boundary differently
because timeout decisions depend on local clock behavior.
end note
@enduml
